# Architecture: DDD + Layered

This project follows **Domain-Driven Design (DDD)** and a **layered architecture**, aligned with **`screen-capture-kit`** and **`speech-kit`** where layering helps, but centered on **this package’s bounded context**: **macOS meeting-style capture UX**, **orchestration**, and **normalized session facts** for the host app. Dependencies flow inward: outer layers depend on inner layers; the **domain** has no dependencies on other layers.

**Sibling packages**: `session_insight_kit` **composes** [`speech_kit`](https://github.com/blendfactory/speech-kit) (on-device speech / `SpeechAnalyzer` pipeline) and [`screen_capture_kit`](https://github.com/blendfactory/screen-capture-kit) (ScreenCaptureKit). Their **native bridges and framework details stay inside those packages**. This repo’s **domain** models **session facts and lifecycle** that *this* package owns; it does **not** re-expose Apple framework types as domain concepts. Map framework and sibling-package outputs at **application** or **infrastructure** boundaries into **domain value objects**.

**Out of scope for all layers**: host-owned **LLM calls**, **prompts**, **minutes templates**, and **summarization**. The public API may emit **structured payloads** the host serializes or passes to a model; the package does not bundle inference or “insights.”

## Layer overview

| Layer | Responsibility | Allowed to depend on |
|-------|----------------|----------------------|
| **Presentation / API** | Flutter capture/recording **widgets**, public exports, barrel | Application, Domain |
| **Application** | Session use cases: orchestrate `speech_kit` + `screen_capture_kit`, map streams to domain, emit session bundle | Domain, (optional) ports / infrastructure interfaces |
| **Domain** | Session identity, timeline, transcript segments (normalized), artifact references, session events, domain errors | Nothing (pure Dart; no `dart:io` / `dart:ffi` / platform / Flutter) |
| **Infrastructure** | Adapters to sibling packages, platform glue, `MethodChannel` / FFI **only if** not already covered by `speech_kit` / `screen_capture_kit` | Domain, Application (implements ports) |

**Note**: “Presentation” includes **library UI** presented to the app (widgets and affordances), not only type-only “API contract” surfaces. **Domain** remains Flutter-free so session logic and types stay testable without binding to widgets.

**Intended use cases**: Meeting-style **display or window** capture, **audio path** selection within platform limits, **clear recording state**, **multiplexed or demuxed** outputs (host-selectable), and **downstream-ready** artifacts plus a **consistent time base** for transcript segments and events. See the repository README (`package vs host`, session flow, and “analysis foundation” sections).

## Consumer guidance (Flutter apps on macOS)

- **Entry point**: Prefer one import `package:session_insight_kit/session_insight_kit.dart` and a facade such as **`SessionInsightKit`** (name may evolve with the first public API).
- **Typical flow**: configure **sources and output mode** → **start session** → consume **normalized segment and session events** during recording → **stop** → receive **artifact paths and session bundle** suitable for host pipelines. Use `try/finally` or `async` cleanup so underlying capture and speech sessions always end deterministically (delegate teardown rules to the sibling packages where applicable).
- **DI and testing**: Inject the facade or application ports; substitute fakes for **session lifecycle** and **stream mapping** without spinning real capture/speech.
- **Platform and errors**: **macOS only** for the intended capture model; on unsupported contexts, throw **`UnsupportedError`**. Map permission, capture, and analyzer failures to a **`SessionInsightKitException`** (or equivalent **domain** error) at the boundary—do not leak raw framework error types from the public surface.

