## Domain model (aggregate, entities, value objects)

When **`doc/domain-model.md`** exists, treat it as the detailed source of truth. Until then, align with the README: one **session** is the natural **consistency boundary**—from **configure** through **stop**, producing **artifacts** and a **session bundle** of **facts** (provenance, timeline, segments, events).

- **Aggregate root (conceptual)**: **`RecordingSession`** (name TBD)—**lifecycle** and **correlation id** for everything emitted in one run: capture, speech-derived segments, and artifact catalog **as modeled by this package**.
- **Entities**: Prefer **value-object-heavy** design initially; add entities only when a concept needs **stable identity** beyond the session (e.g. long-lived user preferences might live in the **host**, not this package).
- **Value objects**: **Extension types** for opaque handles (e.g. **`SessionId`**); **immutable classes** for **transcript segments**, **time ranges**, **artifact references**, and **session events**. These types describe **what was recorded and derived**, not **why** or **what the host should ask an LLM**.

